.TH GWEB 1 "2026-07-17" "GWEB" "GWEB Manual"
.SH NAME
gtangle, gweave \- translate GWEB to Go and/or TeX
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gtangle
.RB [ \-o
.IR dir ]
.IR webfile [ .w ]
.RI [ changefile [ .ch ]]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
.B gweave
.RB [ \-o
.IR dir ]
.IR webfile [ .w ]
.RI [ changefile [ .ch ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B gtangle
program converts a GWEB source document into a Go program that may be compiled
in the usual way. It expands the named\-section references in program order and
runs
.BR gofmt (1)
on the result. The output file includes
.B //line
directives so that debugging can be done in terms of the GWEB source file; as
with CWEB's
.B #line
specifications, they are always emitted.
.PP
The
.B gweave
program converts the same GWEB file into a TeX file that may be formatted and
printed in the usual way. It takes appropriate care of typographic details like
page layout and the use of indentation,
.IR italics ,
.BR boldface ,
etc., and it supplies extensive cross\-index information that it gathers
automatically.
.PP
GWEB allows you to prepare a single document containing all the information
that is needed both to produce a compilable Go program and to produce a
well\-formatted document describing the program in as much detail as the writer
may desire. The user of GWEB ought to be familiar with TeX as well as Go. GWEB
is modeled closely on Knuth and Levy's CWEB, with C replaced by Go:
.B gtangle
is the analogue of
.BR ctangle (1),
.B gweave
of
.BR cweave (1).
.SH USAGE
The command line should have one or two names on it. The first is taken as the
GWEB input file (and
.B .w
is added if there is no extension). If there is a second name, it is a change
file (and
.B .ch
is added if there is no extension). The change file overrides parts of the GWEB
file, as described in the documentation.
.PP
.B gtangle
writes the unnamed
.B @c
sections to the input's base name with a
.B .go
extension. Sections introduced with
.BI @( file @>=
are written to their own named files instead, so one web can emit several files
(and a
.BR go.mod ).
.B gweave
writes the input's base name with a
.B .tex
extension. Use
.B \-o
to send the output elsewhere.
.PP
The woven file begins with
.B \einput gwebmac
\(em
.B gweave
supplies this line itself \(em so the
.B .w
file need not. Process the result with a TeX engine that can find
.IR gwebmac.tex :
.PP
.RS
.EX
pdftex file.tex          # -> file.pdf, with hyperlinks and bookmarks
.EE
.RE
.PP
For the DVI route, request the dvipdfmx hyperlink back end with
.BR \elet\epdf+ ,
exactly as in CWEB:
.PP
.RS
.EX
tex "\elet\epdf+ \einput file.tex"
dvipdfmx file.dvi        # -> file.pdf, with hyperlinks and bookmarks
.EE
.RE
.PP
A plain
.B tex
run with no
.B \epdf
produces a DVI without links.
.PP
As they run, both programs print a banner line and a brief progress report to
standard error, one
.BI * N
per starred (chapter) section.
.SH OPTIONS
The options are common to both
.B gtangle
and
.BR gweave :
.TP
.BI \-o " dir"
Write output files to
.I dir
instead of the input file's directory. For
.BR gtangle ,
the directory (and any subdirectories named by
.BI @( file @>=
targets) is created if necessary.
.TP
.B \-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TEXINPUTS
Point this at a directory holding
.IR gwebmac.tex ,
or copy the file next to your document, so the TeX engine can find the macro
package. The installer places
.I gwebmac.tex
in your TeX tree, so this is not normally needed. See
.BR tex (1)
for the details of the searching.
.SH FILES
The location of the files mentioned below varies from system to system. Use the
.B kpsewhich
utility to find their locations.
.TP
.I gwebmac.tex
The TeX macros
.B \einput
in the first line of the
.B gweave
output file (the analogue of CWEB's
.IR cwebmac.tex ).
.TP
.I kotexgweb.tex
Korean localization: fonts and the LuaTeX PDF back end. Add
.B \einput kotexgweb
to a web's limbo to use it.
.TP
.I gwebman.tex
The GWEB user manual, together with the
.B .w
file\-format reference in
.IR format.md .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gofmt (1),
.BR pdftex (1),
.BR dvipdfmx (1),
.BR tex (1)
.PP
.BR ctangle (1),
.BR cweave (1),
.BR cweb (1)
\(em the C system GWEB is modeled on.
.PP
The GWEB manual and source: <https://github.com/sjnam/gweb>.
.SH AUTHORS
Don Knuth wrote WEB for TeX and Pascal. Silvio Levy designed and developed CWEB
by adapting the WEB conventions to C; Knuth began using CWEB and made further
refinements.
.PD 0
.P
.PD
GWEB adapts those conventions to Go and is maintained by sjnam
<https://github.com/sjnam>.
